      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">courtney</cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2007/03/into-the-pantry/#comment-6239"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2007-03-20T15:01:00-04:00">Tuesday, March 20, 2007 at 3:01 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>OH I can&#8217;t wait to try this. I bought some lentils a couple of months ago for the first time, but haven&#8217;t tried them because I didn&#8217;t know what to do with them. But now I do. </></>If you are ready for spring and summer, may I suggest that you look for ugly ripe tomatos. They are grown here in Florida, and are pretty darn good for a dead of winter Florida tomato. I believe whole foods is supposed to carry them. </></>Right now is one of my favorite times of year though, as it is usually in the 80&#8217;s and sunny.</p>
    </div>

