    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>wow. We&#8217;re cooking on the same wavelength on the two outer coasts.  I stumbled upon Claudia Rosen&#8217;s original Middle Eastern cookbook a few weekends ago and have been completely smitten with it ever since. I&#8217;ve cooked at least a half dozen recipes out of it in that time and they&#8217;re all winners.</></>I also came up with my own version of  mujadara recently, using just ginger, onions and cayenne.  It&#8217;s ridiculously good, and, just like yours, better the next day, and even more delicious cold.  Good stuff this Middle Eastern cuisine.</p>
