      <a href="https://orangette.net/2007/03/into-the-pantry/#comment-6298"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2009-12-28T16:10:35-05:00">Monday, December 28, 2009 at 4:10 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Yes, the name for this is &#39;mdardra&#39;. mjadara is a similar recipe-rice, onions, lentils&#8211;but it is pureed at the end, and eaten with bread. also, i dont quite understand why it took so long to brown the onions. i make this often and it takes five minutes tops on high heat.<br />also, yes cumin really brings out the taste of the lentils.</p>
    </div>

