    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="https://www.blogger.com/profile/18278895757317443494" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">nicole</a></cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2007/03/into-the-pantry/#comment-6302"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2010-09-28T15:46:57-04:00">Tuesday, September 28, 2010 at 3:46 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>OH MY GOD, this recipe is so wonderful and simple!!! I come very late to the Mujadara party, but I needed to tell you how much I enjoyed this. I made a few mods following some of the comments:</p>
<p>&#8211; made twice as many onions, and serve half of them as a garnish on top. (I&#39;m a bit obsessed with caramelized onions.)<br />&#8211; added half a stick of cinnamon and 1 tsp. of cumin at the &#8220;rice&#8221; stage.<br />&#8211; added lemon and a bit of fleur de sel at the end<br />&#8211; served with wedges of za&#39;atar-sprinkled toasted pitas, and a cucumber/mint salad.</p>
<p>SO SO SO GOOD!!!! Perfect autumn dish.</p>
    </div>

